    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 2em auto;
    max-width: 42em;
    padding: 0 1em;
  }
  h1 { color: #2A7F8C; font-weight: 600; }
  h3 { color: #2A7F8C; margin-top: 1.5em; }
  a { color: #FF7F66; text-decoration: none; }
  a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  code, pre {
    background: #E6F4EE;
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: .3em .6em;
    font-size: 90%;
  }
  footer {
    font-size: .9em;
    color: #4B6043;
    margin-top: 3em;
    border-top: 1px solid #C3E8CB;
    padding-top: 1em;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Crisis‑Chat Quick Guide – Version History</h1>
<p>This record tracks design and accessibility updates for the Crisis‑Chat Quick Guide.  
Lifeline information is verified quarterly (<strong>988</strong> · <a href="https://findahelpline.com" target="_blank">findahelpline.com</a>).</p>

<h3>v1.0 · 2024‑07‑12</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Initial release: Ocean, Dawn, and Forest palettes finalized</li>
  <li>Lifeline details added (988 / findahelpline.com)</li>
  <li>Phone and desktop layouts created</li>
</ul>

<h3>v1.1 · 2024‑09‑03</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Text hierarchy and spacing updates for legibility</li>
  <li>Added dark‑mode variant</li>
  <li>Accessibility checklist included (contrast ≥ 4.5 : 1)</li>
</ul>

<h3>v1.2 · 2024‑11‑15</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Export sizes & compression settings refined</li>
  <li>Footer attribution guidance added</li>
  <li>File‑naming standard documented</li>
